Deploy your site to an ultra-redundant global CDN that‚Äôs purpose built for serving pages and assets quickly and consistently.

### Automate deployment
Netlify‚Äôs built-in Continuous Deployment automatically runs your build commands and deploys the result whenever you push to your Git repository.

### Add a custom domain
Purchase domains and manage DNS zones and records right inside of Netlify.

### HTTPS is automatic
Your site will automatically be secured with a free TLS certificate from Let‚Äôs Encrypt.

### Deploy Previews

issue.title: Refactor Firebase initialization into dedicated module for better security and organization
issue.body:
This PR refactors the Firebase initialization code to improve security and code organization by extracting it from `src/App.jsx` into a dedicated `src/firebase.js` module.

## Changes Made

### üîß **Firebase Module Creation**
- Created `src/firebase.js` as the centralized Firebase initialization module
- Exports `db`, `auth`, and the Firebase `app` instance for use across components
- Maintains existing environment variable configuration using `import.meta.env.VITE_*` variables

### üîÑ **Import Refactoring** 
- Updated `src/App.jsx` to import Firebase services from the new module instead of initializing Firebase directly
- Updated component files (`EmployeePTOHistoryPage.jsx`, `EmployeePTORequestForm.jsx`) to use centralized Firebase imports
- Removed duplicate Firebase initialization code across components

### üìù **Enhanced Documentation**
- Improved `.env.example` with detailed step-by-step instructions for obtaining Firebase configuration values
- Added security notes emphasizing that actual `.env` files should never be committed
- Included direct links to Firebase Console for easier setup

## Security Benefits

- **Centralized Configuration**: All Firebase config is now in one secure location
- **Environment Variable Usage**: Continues to use Vite's `import.meta.env` for secure config loading
- **No Secrets Committed**: Verified that only placeholder values exist in the repository
- **Proper `.gitignore`**: `.env` files remain excluded from version control

## Before/After

**Before**: Firebase was initialized directly in `App.jsx` and duplicated in component files
```javascript
// In App.jsx and components
import { getFirestore } from 'firebase/firestore';
const db = getFirestore();
```

**After**: Centralized Firebase initialization with clean imports
```javascript
// In firebase.js
export const db = getFirestore(app);

// In components
import { db } from './firebase.js';
```

This refactoring maintains all existing functionality while improving code organization and following Firebase best practices for modular applications.

issue.title: PS2 dont work but still visible
issue.body:
### Quick summary

Buzzers are detected by the system, but running them causes the errors seen in the log. When starting the game as well as during the language selection menu in Buzz!‚Ñ¢: Quiz World [BCES00647] the buzzers flash red.

### Details

On the last build I tested (around two weeks ago), the game ran fine and loaded into gameplay without issues. After updating, it now gets stuck during the loading sequence every single time. I tested the same game on my actual PS3 and it loads normally, so this doesn‚Äôt seem to be a problem with the game files themselves.

I‚Äôve tried clearing cache, switching between Vulkan and OpenGL, and even deleting/re-installing the game data, but the issue still happens.


### Attach a log file

[log.txt](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/21822950/log.txt)

### Attach capture files for visual issues

Graphically, everything looks normal up until the freeze ‚Äî no visual glitches or artifacts appear. The game audio also cuts out at the exact moment it hangs.

### System configuration

OS: macOS Sequoia 15.x (latest)
	‚Ä¢	CPU: Apple M1 (base variant, 8-core)
	‚Ä¢	GPU: Integrated Apple GPU (M1)
	‚Ä¢	RAM: 8GB Unified Memory
